post_text:
Kankakee School District Early Childhood Educators gathered at Proegler for the third day of training for Sunshine Circles.

According to their website, "Sunshine Circles are adult-directed, structured play therapy-based groups that incorporate playful, cooperative, and nurturing activities that enhance the emotional well-being of children. Instead of talking about positive social behavior, the group leaders and children DO positive social interaction."
For more information, visit https://theraplay.org/training/training-programs/sunshine-circles/

District 111 is excited to launch our own JROTC program! Check out the video and sign up for the Zoom info session to find out more.

Sign up for the Zoom information session
at the following link:
https://ksd111.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_NilkDxiaS2aQQXQEyWaFoA

* What is Army JROTC?
A leadership and service learning course.

* Why should you join Army JROTC?
To learn the Army values: Loyalty, Duty, Respect,
Selfless Service, Honor, Integrity, Personal Courage
and learn valuable skills for high school
and beyond!

* Who should attend this Zoom session?
Incoming 9th and 10th graders and parents
interested in learning more!

Date/Time: Thursday, July 23, 6:30 pm

post_text:
Kindergarten openings are available in Kankakee School District‚Äôs Math Inc. Magnet at Steuben! This Magnet has a unique atmosphere where students invent, understand and remember mathematical ideas. Math Inc. features a Math Lab that is conducive to small group interactive, hands on activities that build concrete understanding of everyday math concepts. Our community of excited learners engage with the use of manipulatives to solve everyday problems. Beginning as early as Kindergarten our students have the opportunity to engage in business projects and work towards a common goal. All students have the opportunity to plan, create and execute a product to earn money and choose how to spend their profits!! Students are exposed to age appropriate product creation, finances, advertising, marketing, selling, fulfilling and distributing orders.

You can apply at ksd111.schoolmint.net

https://ksd111.schoolmint.net/signin

To clear up any misunderstanding, the Board of Education President does not make the posts on the Kankakee School District Facebook page.

I, Bill Yohnka, mistakenly posted letters today from the Board President without addresses erased. I corrected that mistake shortly after. That was my mistake not the Board President‚Äôs. I apologize for that.

I would hope that people could keep a level head and try to stay focused on serving our youth and let adult disagreements go.

Again, I apologize for my mistake.

Kankakee High School International Thespian Society Virtual Induction Ceremony

Kankakee High School Drama
May 11 at 5:01 PM ¬∑

This year we were so excited to bring back the KHS chapter of the International Thespian society, after a couple of decades hiatus. shared_text:
Kennedy Middle School
April 22 at 5:48 PM ¬∑

Happy Earth Day! For the past few weeks Kennedy students have been learning about land artist Andy Goldsworthy and found object artist Tony Cragg. Both artists have ties to the environment: Goldsworthy creates art using only natural materials like rocks, sticks, and leaves; Cragg‚Äôs early work was made using found objects as an act of recycling and reusing found and discarded materials.

While students are home, art supplies may be limited, if there are any at all. Using natural and found materials is an accessible alternative to traditional art materials like paint and color pencils.

Here are a couple examples of student projects (a nature mandala and rock stack by 5th grader Miles Yohnka) and Mr. Costanza‚Äôs found object sun, an example for students made with his sons in his back yard.

The earth is a beautiful canvas!

We love our teachers!

Thanks to Karen Dannenhauer who secured a grant that was to be used to purchase learning materials for kids to keep at home. She created kits that include magnetic letters and numbers with a cookie sheet to use as a work surface, scissors, crayons, glue sticks, pencils, paper, teddy bear counters for counting and sorting, a puzzle, playdough, and some of the kids got rhyming pair puzzles -- as needed for ages and goals.

shared_text:
Kankakee School District Robotics Team
March 28 at 6:37 PM ¬∑

I am so proud of the time that my son put in with me over the past couple of days to protect and help our community! Many of our friends and family in this community do not have the supplies they need due to the Covid 19 pandemic. Medical visors for the hospitals are one of those things. We are proud to donate 23 visors to Riverside's ER after some drafting, 3 prototypes, cutting, filing, stringing, and cleaning. We all appreciate you being on the front lines for us. Stay strong! Kankakee Strong!

I am updating this post with information to make the visors:
Medical Visor PDF: (https://drive.google.com/open?id=15GD5_ZlBUpbuHUYcdMBCKCenRZ_b3glM)
Medical Visor Slides: (https://drive.google.com/open?id=1tvuc9qZQ1ZrmCjtge4wlVgnmBDDG8D-WJdOq5Bz6oiA)
Amazon Materials List : (https://www.amazon.com/gp/registry/wishlist/HFM5AFISYUKP/ref=cm_wl_huc_view)
Drafting STL File: (https://drive.google.com/open?id=19nmH97IXOiMLOmV1kMgM1MzlkVrq1s6E)

shared_text:
Kankakee County Health Department
March 27 at 4:26 PM ¬∑

Facts Over Fear #6:

Have you been seeing the below post on social media recently? This is a MYTH in Kankakee County. Riverside Healthcare and AMITA St. Mary's Hospital have confirmed their limited visitor restriction policies. However, if a child is brought in through the Emergency Department and/or is an inpatient, one parent/guardian is allowed to stay with the child. If necessary, proper PPE would be provided to the parent as well. Be comforted knowing your child will not be alone!

Kankakee County Health Department

Facts Over Fear #6:

However, if a child is brought in through the Emergency Department and/or is an inpatient, one parent/guardian is allowed to stay with the child. If necessary, proper PPE would be provided to the parent as well. Be comforted knowing your child will not be alone!

post_text:
Youth and Government:

Five students from Kankakee High School went to Springfield this past weekend. Maggie Mulcahy, Miguel Espinoza, Jamie Pazino, Isaac Stipp, and Logan Morris have been working since December on learning about all aspects of how government works. The students came up with proposals for bills and ways to lobby for them. These five students went with their proposals to Springfield to partake in the Annual Youth and Government Assembly. As part of the event students from all over the state participate in a mock government.
Organizers are excited to help more Kankakee students be part of the program next year.

Maggie Mulcahy: Legislative Assistant
Miguel Espinoza: Video Media Press
Jamie Pazino: Video Media Press
Isaac Stipp: Lobbyist
Logan Morris: Video Media Press

post_text:
Parents and Guardians:

The KCC Trio/Upward Bound Program will be held at Kankakee High School beginning Wednesday, February 5, 2020 (please see the attached flier for the complete listing of dates). This program will take place from 2:30 p.m.- 4:30 p.m. Your student must be registered with Trio/Upward Bound to participate. If you are not sure if your student is a participant please contact Rhonda Sykes via email at rsykes@kcc.edu with your students first and last name and current year at KHS. Please see the attached flyers for more information regarding the programs.There will be an activity bus available to transport your student home. If your student does not utilize the KHS activity bus your student must have their own transportation home at 4:30 p.m. with no exceptions.

Thank you,
KHS Administration
